Overview Notes: Your liver enzymes are most likely raised as a side effect of taking a statin. Please repeat the levels in January. We can add some liver support in the form of milk thistle and supplement with co-enzymeQ10.
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Your liver enzymes are most likely raised as a side effect of taking a statin. Please repeat the levels in January. We can add some liver support in the form of milk thistle and supplement with co-enzymeQ10.

Overview Notes: Cholesterol: continue taking simvastatin - manage with lifestyle factors. Exercise. Watch carbs, processed and fried food in your diet, manage stress levels and take omega 3 2g daily. Repeat in 3/12
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Overview Notes: Cholesterol: continue taking simvastatin - manage with lifestyle factors. Exercise. Watch carbs, processed and fried food in your diet, manage stress levels and take omega 3 2g daily. Repeat in 3/12
Comment Key: ClinicalExamNote
Comment Value: Normal examination
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Men's Health Recommendations: Monitor and visit your doctor if you experience any urinary symptoms.
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Your liver enzymes are most likely raised as a side effect of taking a statin. Please repeat the levels in January. We can add some liver support in the form of milk thistle and supplement with co-enzymeQ10.
Comment Key: CurrentComplaintNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Your liver enzymes are most likely raised as a side effect of taking a statin. Please repeat the levels in January. We can add some liver support in the form of milk thistle and supplement with co-enzymeQ10.
Comment Key: CurrentComplaintRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Normal examination on the day.

Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Your liver enzymes are most likely raised as a side effect of taking a statin. Please repeat the levels in January. We can add some liver support in the form of milk thistle and supplement with co-enzymeQ10.

Clinical Recommendations: Normal examination on the day.
Men's Health Recommendations: Monitor and visit your doctor if you experience any urinary symptoms.
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Your liver enzymes are most likely raised as a side effect of taking a statin. Please repeat the levels in January. We can add some liver support in the form of milk thistle and supplement with co-enzymeQ10.
Comment Key: MentalHealthMoodRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Men's Health Recommendations: Monitor and visit your doctor if you experience any urinary symptoms.
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Your liver enzymes are most likely raised as a side effect of taking a statin. Please repeat the levels in January. We can add some liver support in the form of milk thistle and supplement with co-enzymeQ10.
Comment Key: MentalHealthStressRecommendation

Overview Notes: Cholesterol: continue taking simvastatin - manage with lifestyle factors. Exercise. Watch carbs, processed and fried food in your diet, manage stress levels and take omega 3 2g daily. Repeat in 3/12
Comment Key: VitalsRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Overview Notes: Non smoker, Frequent exercise Good body composition
HsCRP of 0.6 indicating low levels of inflammation and low heart disease risk
Comment Key: VitaminsOrSupplements

Overview Notes: Your liver enzymes are most likely raised as a side effect of taking a statin. Please repeat the levels in January. We can add some liver support in the form of milk thistle and supplement with co-enzymeQ10.
Comment Key: WomensHealthNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil
